# Helper module for issue #219 regression. Exports a `repeat` that
# returns a `String` — the same bare name `list.repeat` (in the core
# stdlib) exports against `[a]`. Loaded as `--prelude
# issue_219_typer_modcall_lib.kai` so the module table has both
# `list.repeat` and `issue_219_typer_modcall_lib.repeat` registered
# under the bare key `repeat`.
#
# Before issue #219 fix: `list.repeat(0, 3)` typed against whichever
# `repeat` scheme `ty_env_lookup` returned first (the helper's,
# since it's loaded last), so the call rejected with
# `expected: (String, Int) -> String, found: (Int, Int) -> ?t`.
# After the fix: the EModCall branch consults the `<mod>::<fname>`
# qualified key first and resolves correctly.
#
# `repeat` is implemented as a tag-prefixed identity to keep the
# fixture allocation-bound and avoid any bare-name self-recursion
# (which would mask the typer-side bug under test).
pub fn repeat(s: String, n: Int) : String =
  string_concat("[lib]", string_concat(s, int_to_string(n)))
